By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Senate Adhoc Committee on Nigeria Security Challenges is in a closed-door meeting with  the Service Chiefs. The details of the meeting is not yet known as at the time of filing this report, but Sundiata Post recalls that the meeting is coming barely 24 hours after the National  Security Adviser (NSA), Mohammed Monguno, raised the alarm on the deteriorating protocol in the presidency and the renewed attack by Boko   Haram insurgence and bandit in the North West and the North East. Recall also that the bandits yesterday attacked train passenger coming to Abuja from Kaduna. Details of the meeting remain sketchy as at the time of filling this report as Journalists were barred from entering. Details later 